# Work Order Protocol (Always Active)

## Work Order Lifecycle

```
Phase 0: Research    → Dependencies, impact analysis, test plan
Phase 1+: Implement  → Code + tests per phase
Phase N: Audit       → gate-runner.sh wo_exit
Phase N+1: Commit    → Only if gates pass
```

## Required WO Sections

Every Work Order file must contain:
1. **Objective** — What and why
2. **Acceptance Criteria** — Definition of done
3. **Tasks/Phases** — Implementation breakdown
4. **Status** — Current state (Draft/Active/Complete/Blocked)

## WO File Naming

<!-- ADAPT: Use project's slug -->
`WO-$PROJECT_SLUG-NNN.md` in `docs/planning/`

## Single Tracker

All WO status tracked in `docs/planning/WO-INDEX.md`.
- One file, one source of truth
- No separate trackers, no parity checking
- Update WO-INDEX.md every time a WO changes status

## Commit Protocol

- Reference WO number in commit messages: `feat(wo-NNN): description`
- Run quality gates before committing: `bash scripts/gate-runner.sh pre_commit`
- No commits without passing blocking gates
